name: Automotive
description: The automotive industry began in the 1860s with hundreds of manufacturers pioneering the horseless carriage.

name: Beauty
description: One difficulty in understanding beauty is that it has both objective and subjective aspects: it is seen as a property of things but also as depending on the emotional response.

name: Books
description: As a conceptual object, a book refers to a written work of substantial length, which may be distributed either physically or digitally as an ebook.

name: Electronics
description: The next big technological step took several decades to appear, when the first working point-contact transistor was invented by John Bardeen and Walter Houser Brattain.

name: Fashion
description: The most obvious function of clothing is to protect the wearer from the elements. It serves to prevent wind damage and provides protection from sunburn.

name: Furniture
description: People have been using natural objects, such as tree stumps, rocks and moss, as furniture since the beginning of human civilization and continues today in some households/campsites.

name: Jewelry
description: Jewellery may be made from a wide range of materials. Gemstones and similar materials such as amber and coral, precious metals, beads, and shells have been widely used.

name: Toys
description: The origin of toys is prehistoric; dolls representing infants, animals, and soldiers, as well as representations of tools used by adults, are readily found at archaeological sites.
